<div class="story"><p>High on a sandy ridge in Duck sits the subdivision of Osprey, with 43 building lots spread out along Nor Banks Drive. The community has an active home owners association and an association fee used to maintain the private roads, community pool and beach access. The properties on the top of the ridge have panoramic ocean and sound views. The properties along the southern edge of the subdivision abut the <a href="http://frf.usace.army.mil/" title="Field Research Pier">Field Research Pier</a> property which offers ocean and sound views across the un built government property. To the north is the sister subdivision of <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/sea-ridge.asp" title="Sea Ridge">Sea Ridge</a>. </p> <p><a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/osprey-covenants.pdf" title="Osprey Covenants">Osprey Covenants</a> & <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/osprey-architectural-guidelines.pdf" title="Osprey Architectural Guidelines">Osprey Architectural Guidelines</a> & <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/osprey-pool-guidelines.pdf" title="Osprey Pool Guidelines">Osprey Pool Guidelines</a>    - - - <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/Covenant-Disclaimer.asp" target="_blank"><b>    *</b></a></p>
